structures.commons

Interface LinearDataStructure<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Generic Type
    All Superinterfaces:
    DataStructure<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IndexedDataStructure<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayList, ChainedDataStructure, ChainedIndexedDataStructure, DynamicallySizedArray, LinkedList, Queue, Stack

    public interface LinearDataStructure<T>
extends DataStructure<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Interface for all linear DataStructures such as LinkedList, ArrayList, or any other vector-like data structure.

      • equivalentTo

        default boolean equivalentTo(java.lang.Object object)
        Determines whether or not an Object is equal to this LinearDataStructure. Implementing classes can override the java.lang.Object.equals() method, and call this. useful: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/overriding-equals-method-in-java/
        Parameters:
        object - Object to compare this object with.
        Returns:
        True if the objects are of the same type, their sizes are the same, and they contain all the same values.
